d to be grouped.  If you really want mages to be more desirable to groups, let them summon no drop items that have a right click group wide effect. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqhue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qhue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/02 9:42:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10400.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Casters arent lazy</span><hr size=1> This quote REALLY irks me:<br><br>&quot;Quit being lazy, go out and kill some mob bosses.&quot;<br><br>FFS we HAVE been killing bosses.  Dont fault the casters because Verant, until last week, had no concept of what a useful item to a caster would be.<br><br>Its all well and good to say &quot;oh well just go back and retrochange caster gear to have focus effects&quot;<br><br>Just what caster gear would you change?  Who would you hire to go through the database and change all the items assuming you DID manage to find a set of caster-items that were deemed &quot;focus worthy&quot; <br><br>Real Focus Items will indeed be dropped by uber mobs, but they arent in yet and the mage-summoned set gives casters a needed boost NOW to make up for getting $#$@ for the past 2 years. <br><br>If they had made the current focus items drop off say Trakanon then everyone here would be whining : &quot;@#$@$ Verant, now we cant go kill the Avatar of War after the patch because all the whining casters want us to fight with 45 other guilds to kill Trakanon when we havent had ANY desire or need to kill Trakanon in over a year...good job you dumb #$%#&quot;<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugallerus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallerus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/02 9:49:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10400.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some focus item effects changed with 3/21 patch</span><hr size=1> Summoned focus items are dumb - they do nothing to help caster balance or mages in particular...unless you count me having to log on my mage at the beginning of playing to summon crap for people for the night.<br><br>Caster balancing is kinda of dumb too, the only classes that need help are low-mid level damage based int casters (and this is only true because meele is ridiculously easy to twink), high level (50+) pet casters (cause their pets dont scale &amp; pathing sux in a lotta zones) and raid level enchanters (although I think the hate removing/adding spells are a good addition for them).<br><br>Solution to caster problems: make pet power scale better post 50+ &amp; add more level minimums to high end weapons and armor to stop twinking.  Give high level enchanters or some ability to use their epic on a group basis...hasting everyone on a raid is sooooo tedious.  Some alternative to tash would be nice too, cause tashicide on every uber mob gets old fast.<br><br>All focus items do for casters is make them more a little more powerful - which means VI will simply tune encounters to that level of power...focus items will not change &quot;the vision&quot; and its requirements for x number of players for encounter_01, etc (this is the real reason for all of the RoF type encounters imo, its the one way VI has found that forces players to bring the number of players that VI thinks is appropriate for certain encounters) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhactus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hactus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/02 9:54:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10400.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I thought Tashicide was fixed.</span><hr size=1> I was pretty sure that <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/spells/spell.asp?Id=1598">Beguiling Visage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> was the anti-tashicide spell.  Created spefically to prevent Tashicide.<br><br>As for focus items being balancing, we're just going to have to wait to find out.<br><br>Basenji, Unconquered Bard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubearberry.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bearberry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/02 10:03:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10400.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I thought Tashicide was fixed.</span><hr size=1> These items are summoned and therefore easily accessible because they SHOULD have been in game and accumulating since Day 1 of Kunark. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaphyd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aphyd</A></span><br